EXERCISE 1 on page 498:

First compile the program and put the executable code
in the file named pgm.  If you are using the c-shell,
try the following commands:

   vi go                      // so you will know what is in the file

   man source                 // so you will know what the command does

   source go                  // execute the commands in go

   (source go) > output       // capture the results in a file

---
NOTE:

The above suggestions make sense only in a UNIX environment.
